<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-966] Support Replication-enabled MySQL  </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-966</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Starting with Connector/J 3.1.7, a MySQL JDBC driver is available &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;2&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; that will automatically send queries to a read/write master, or a failover or round-robin loadbalanced set of slaves based on the state of Connection.getReadOnly() . &lt;br/&gt;
OpenJPA can take advantage of this driver by setting up read-only property of the connection based on the dirty nature of the current transaction &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://n2.nabble.com/Mysql-Connector-J-ReplicantConnection-tc2431984.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://n2.nabble.com/Mysql-Connector-J-ReplicantConnection-tc2431984.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;2&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.1/en/connector-j-reference-replication-connection.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.1/en/connector-j-reference-replication-connection.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
